{"word":"ὀπώρα","slug":"ὀπώρα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n74691\" key=\"o)pw/ra\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὀπώρ-α</orth>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ion.\">Ion.</a></gram> </gramGrp> <orth extent=\"suff\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὀπώρ-η</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">ἡ</gen> : sts. <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ὁπώρα</orth>, cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">χεῖμα χὠπώραν,</foreign> i.e. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">καὶ ὁπ-,</foreign> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0291.tlg001:76\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Alcm.\">Alcm.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">76</biblScope> </bibl> (<foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">χειμάχωι πάραν,</foreign> etc. codd.) ; pr. nn. <sense id=\"n74691.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">Ὁπωρίς</quote_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ IG\">IG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">5(1).1497</biblScope></bibl></cit>, <title_ TEIform=\"title\">Hopora</title_> <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ CIL\">CIL</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.21782</biblScope> </bibl> ; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μεθόπωρον, μεθοπωρινός</foreign>:—<tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the part of the year between the rising of Sirius and of Arcturus</tr_> (i.e. the last days of July, all Aug., and part of Sept.), <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">the latter part of summer</tr_>; <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl> <pb n=\"1243\" TEIform=\"pb\"/> names <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">θέρος</foreign> and <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀπώρη</foreign> together, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">θέρος τεθαλυῖά τ᾽ ὀπώρη</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:11:192\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">11.192</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> ; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">Σείριος</foreign> being the star of <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀπώρη,</foreign> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:22:27\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">22.27</biblScope> </bibl> ; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ὀπωρινός.</foreign>—In later times it became the name of a definite season, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">autumn</tr_> (v. <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ὥρα</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:1:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1.1</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> c), but was still used sts. to denote <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">summer</tr_> (autumn being distd. as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">φθινόπωρον</foreign> or <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μετόπωρον</foreign>)<cit TEIform=\"cit\"><quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">, ἀρξάμενος ἀπὸ τοῦ ἠρινοῦ χρόνου πρὸ ὀπώρας</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg001.perseus-grc1:3:2:10\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ X.\">X.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ HG\">HG</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3.2.10</biblScope></bibl></cit>, cf. <bibl n